devdoc.details: Uses FHE to store encrypted data and perform encrypted analysis on-chain

params.habitProof: The FHE proof for habit completion encryption
params.moodProof: The FHE proof for mood encryption

params.encryptedHabits: Array of encrypted habit completion rates (0-100)
params.habitProofs: Array of FHE proofs for habit completion encryption
params.moodProofs: Array of FHE proofs for mood encryption

getAnalysisTotals(address,uint256).details: This allows encrypted analysis by returning totals that can be decrypted and analyzed client-sideNote: Not view because FHE operations modify state (permissions)

params.recordCount: Number of recent records to analyze (up to 10 for MVP)

returns.encryptedTotalHabits: The encrypted sum of habit completions

params.numDays: The number of recent days to average (max 30)

getHabitCompletionTrend(address,uint256).details: Client-side can decrypt and interpret trend direction

params.recordCount: Number of recent records to analyze (up to 10 for MVP)

returns.encryptedTrendSlope: Slope of habit completion trend (positive = improving)

getMoodHabitCorrelation(address,uint256).details: Client-side can decrypt and calculate correlation coefficient using these valuesNote: Not view because FHE operations modify state (permissions)

params.recordCount: Number of recent records to analyze (up to 10 for MVP)

returns.encryptedHabitSquared: Sum of (habitCompletion * habitCompletion) for correlation analysis
returns.encryptedMoodHabitProduct: Sum of (mood * habitCompletion) for correlation analysis

returns.earliestTimestamp: The timestamp of the earliest record
returns.latestTimestamp: The timestamp of the latest record

returns.encryptedHabits: Array of encrypted habit completion values

getStressReductionTrend(address,uint256).details: Client-side can compare these to see if mood is improving (stress reducing)Note: Not view because FHE operations modify state (permissions)

params.recordCount: Number of recent records to analyze (up to 10 for MVP)

returns.averageHabit: Average habit completion (0 if no records)
returns.averageMood: Average mood score (0 if no records)
returns.consistencyScore: Consistency score based on regular logging (0-100)

devdoc.title: EncryptedHabitMoodTracker - Private Habit and Mood Tracking

addDailyRecord(bytes32,bytes32,bytes,byt.notice: Add a daily mood and habit completion record

batchAddDailyRecords(bytes32[],bytes32[].notice: Batch add multiple daily records at once

getAnalysisTotals(address,uint256).notice: Calculate total mood and habit completion for analysis

getDailyAverages(address,uint256).notice: Get average mood and habit completion over a period

getDayCount(address).notice: Get the total number of days recorded for a user

getEncryptedHabitCompletion(address,uint.notice: Get the encrypted habit completion for a specific day

getEncryptedMood(address,uint256).notice: Get the encrypted mood for a specific day

getHabitCompletionTrend(address,uint256).notice: Calculate habit completion trend over time

getMoodHabitCorrelation(address,uint256).notice: Calculate correlation between mood improvement and habit completion

getRecordTimestamp(address,uint256).notice: Get timestamp for a specific day record

getRecordTimestampRange(address).notice: Get timestamp range for user's records

getRecordsInRange(address,uint256,uint25.notice: Get records within a date range

getStressReductionTrend(address,uint256).notice: Calculate stress reduction trend (lower mood = higher stress, so we track if mood is improving)

recordExists(address,uint256).notice: Check if a record exists for a specific day

userdoc.notice: Allows users to record encrypted mood (1-5) and habit completion rate (0-100) privately
